        <div class="collapse txt_burnoff inner" style="font-family:Roboto-light">
            <h2> Burn-off(planned burn)</h2>
            <p style="text-align:justify;">
                To avoid the spread of bushfire, Burn off the grass, weeds, stubble, undergrowth or vegetation.
                These burn off without permission can result in fines of up to $20,000 and/or 12 months imprisonment.
                Moreover check up with your local council to know the laws for lighting fires and burning rubbish.
                Unregistered burn-offs can cause brigades to be called out unnecessarily.

            </p>
            <h2> Burn-off checklist</h2>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    Check and follow local regulations or laws set down
                    by CFA or your local council.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Notify neighbours at least two hours before
                    starting the burn.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Notify VicFire on <strong>1800 668 511</strong>
                </li>
                <li>
                    Check the weather forecast for the day of the
                    burn and a few days afterwards.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Check the fuel moisture conditions.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Establish a fire break of no less than three metres
                    cleared of all flammable material.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Make sure there are enough resources on hand to monitor,
                    contain and extinguish the burn safely and effectively.
                </li>


            </ul>

            <h2> Register your burn-off</h2>
            <p>Prior notify the Emergency Services Telecommunications Authority (ESTA) of your planned burn</p>
            <ul>
                <li><div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-11">
                            By  Email: Fill the <a target="_blank" href="@Url.Action("Burnoff","Home")" style="color:red">Burn-off Notify permit</a> and email to <a style="color:red; padding-right:5%;" href="burnoffs@esta.vic.gov.au"> burnoffs@esta.vic.gov.au</a>

                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-1">
                            <form target="_blank" action="@Url.Action("Burnoff","Home")">
                                <input style="background-color:peru;border-block-color:#00000050;border-radius:5px; font-weight:bold;" type="submit" value="Fill the Form" />
                            </form>
                        </div>
                    </div>



                </li>


                <li> By Phone:  Register your burn-off by calling ESTA on <strong>1800 668 511</strong>, 24 hours a day, seven days a week.</li>

            </ul>

        </div>
